@w11114m to customize OpenAPI examples, all is needed is to use a class that inherits from pydantic BaseModel, as specified here: https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/schema-extra-example/
Dependencies are not needed for customizing OpenAPI examples. Dependencies should be used for dependency injection, like for DB connections, as specified here: https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/dependencies/
What are you trying to accomplish with RequestModelFactorySingleton? is it custom types? if so, I would recommend implementing it with pydantic. There are good examples for it here: https://docs.pydantic.dev/usage/types/#custom-data-types

@DavidBord Thanks for the answer!
The fact is that I need to use Depends with a custom class to convert the request parameters into the request body. This needs to be done in Depends to support further pydantic validation of the resulting body.
I understand that this is an atypical implementation, but it is necessary.

For a better understanding, I will leave below a complete example of the RequestModelFactorySingleton class:

```
class RequestModelFactorySingleton(object):
    _models = {}

    def __new__(cls, model: BaseModel):
        if not cls._models.get(id(model)):
            cls._models[id(model)] = cls.query_processing_factory(model)
        return cls._models.get(id(model))

    @classmethod
    def query_processing_factory(cls, model: BaseModel):
        def processing_function(request: Request, items: model):
            if dict(request.query_params):
                try:
                    serialized_request = {
                        key: cls.transform_to_pyobj_or_return(value) for key, value in dict(request.query_params).items()}
                except json.JSONDecodeError as e:
                    raise ValidException(status.HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST, f'Wrong json: {e}')
                items = items.__class__(**serialized_request)
            return items
        return processing_function

    @staticmethod
    def transform_to_pyobj_or_return(value):
        try:
            value = json.loads(value)
        except json.JSONDecodeError:
            pass
        return value
```

